Rating: 3
I've made this recipe multiple times, and am never disappointed. When I can't find arugula, I usually substitute spinach, I like the mild flavor of that as much or more than the arugula. It's also quick and easy, so it's a nice weeknight dinner.

Rating: 2
just ok. add too much pasta water and you will find it hard to taste the goat cheese. the arugula and mushrooms don't really meld. would have been better with just the mushrooms. my arugula was bitter. perhaps it would be better in the early spring when the arugula always tastes sweeter.

Rating: 3
Also, I found the arugula a little bitter, but I think if I had cut it in smaller pieces that would have been better. Watercress or basil would be good options too.

