I made this in haste, and didn't put enough garlic & salt. I agree, shallots would help. Tasty, but a little bland. I think that was just from my carelessness. I'll make it again with revisions.

Rating: 2
This is a great healthy weeknight meal - even better with whole wheat spaghetti!

Rating: 3
I really enjoyed this dish... light and healthy. Had to make a few changes though. I could not find arugula at the store so substituted watercress. Added more garlic and shallots as another cook suggested. I also used only baby portabella mushrooms because my boyfriend and I are currently addicted to them. Next time I'll top it off with pine nuts.

Rating: 3
Forgot to add to my previous review: I used campanelle pasta, not spaghetti. I think a shape like that--farfalle, penne, rotini--works much better than spaghetti.

Rating: 3
Quick, easy, tasty . . . what more can you ask for? I added a little more garlic and one shallot (chopped) to the mushroom saute, and used 2 oz. more goat cheese, plus probably used a little more than 1/2 cup of the pasta water. Would definitely make again.

Rating: 2
it tasted good but i found this recipe a disappointment. ingredients do not blend well together physically.

Rating: 3
The flavors in this dish were amazing. I used half wild mushrooms(Hen of the Woods) and half baby portabellas. The pasta was a little dry though - not creamy even after adding all the pasta water. Next time I would add several tablespoons of butter to round out the dish. Otherwise fabulous!